Object.Field: IKM Oracle BI to SQL Append

COMPONENT NAME: IKM Oracle BI to SQL Append
AUTHOR: Oracle
DESCRIPTION - Integration Knowledge Module - Integrates data into a ANSI-SQL92 target database from any ANSI-SQL92 compliant staging area. - The target table is populated in truncate / insert mode and can be controlled post integration.
REQUIREMENTS - Requires a Oracle BI data server with the folowwing JDBC property: NQ_SESSION.SELECTPHYSICAL = yes
BASIC CONFIGURATION Requires a Oracle BI data server with the folowwing JDBC property: NQ_SESSION.SELECTPHYSICAL = yes
OPTIONS (Refer to Option descriptions for more information on each option) OBIEE_SQL_PREFIX : This can be set with any valid OBIEE sql prefix. For e.g, set variable EFFECTIVE_DATE='2008-10-01'
LIMITATIONS - TRUNCATE option may not be supported on all DBMS. - Truncating the target table cannot work when the target table is referenced by another table (foreign key) - When using this module with a journalized source table, data are automatically filtered to not include source deletions - The STATIC_CONTROL option calls the Check Knowledge Module to isolate invalid data (if no CKM is set, an error occurs). This option must be set to NO in the case when an Integration Interface populates a TEMPORARY target datastore.
Automatically attempts to insert data into the Target Datastore of the Interface
Commit all data inserted in the target datastore.
Check this option to control the target table after having inserted or updated target data.
Check this option if you wish to truncate the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to delete all the rows of the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to create the target table
